1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,532
Mom!

2
00:00:01,532 --> 00:00:03,392
Who's Atsara?

3
00:00:03,392 --> 00:00:06,524
She's your real mother. She passed away.

4
00:00:07,422 --> 00:00:08,600
Holy shit!

5
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:12,291
This is the song that made Sun fall asleep
and wake up as Solar.

6
00:00:12,291 --> 00:00:14,065
- Huh?
- Are you sure

7
00:00:14,065 --> 00:00:15,588
you want to donate all this stuff?

8
00:00:15,588 --> 00:00:18,304
I'll just keep these.

9
00:00:18,304 --> 00:00:22,110
Solar, we found the song
that makes Sun fall asleep.

10
00:00:22,110 --> 00:00:26,952
After countless failures and mistakes,

11
00:00:26,952 --> 00:00:30,645
we've finally found the solution.

12
00:00:32,663 --> 00:00:35,747
Little lion, we're finally together.

13
00:00:35,747 --> 00:00:38,284
Were you lonely being home alone?

14
00:00:38,284 --> 00:00:40,154
Don't worry about being alone anymore.

15
00:00:40,154 --> 00:00:42,919
I'll introduce you to my cool friends.

16
00:00:42,919 --> 00:00:46,099
And when you're home,
Uncle Pobmek will stay with you.

17
00:00:46,099 --> 00:00:48,228
He looks so funny.

18
00:00:48,228 --> 00:00:50,290
He looks just like a kidnapper.

19
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:54,779
Oh, hey, Uncle!

20
00:00:54,779 --> 00:00:56,158
You're up.

21
00:00:57,138 --> 00:00:59,145
This is the uncle who looks like a kidnapper.

22
00:00:59,145 --> 00:01:01,657
We went to my house yesterday.

23
00:01:01,657 --> 00:01:04,304
I threw paint balloons
with Teacher Pranee too.

24
00:01:09,047 --> 00:01:11,882
Look, Uncle is such a show-off.

25
00:01:11,882 --> 00:01:13,653
It's still early, and he already
wants to show off playing the guitar.

26
00:01:13,653 --> 00:01:16,744
Hey, don't you like this song?

27
00:01:16,744 --> 00:01:19,386
I can play the whole song now, you know?

28
00:01:19,386 --> 00:01:20,748
Really?

29
00:01:20,748 --> 00:01:22,871
We want to hear it.

30
00:02:03,663 --> 00:02:06,678
Good morning, Teacher.

31
00:02:07,459 --> 00:02:10,268
Good morning, boyfriend.

32
00:02:23,769 --> 00:02:26,532
Sun must love this little lion so much.

33
00:02:26,532 --> 00:02:29,884
Since he got him,
he wouldn't let go of his hand.

34
00:02:31,146 --> 00:02:32,571
Yeah.

35
00:02:33,998 --> 00:02:35,976
He probably misses Mom.

36
00:02:41,443 --> 00:02:42,954
Are you okay?

37
00:02:47,168 --> 00:02:48,696
Of course.

38
00:02:53,162 --> 00:02:55,695
I'm so glad you're strong.

39
00:02:56,451 --> 00:03:01,268
Your strength encourages me.

40
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:04,682
Really?

41
00:03:06,657 --> 00:03:09,082
Then come and get your encouragement.

42
00:03:12,258 --> 00:03:13,452
What's with all this?

43
00:03:13,452 --> 00:03:14,749
We'll see each other every day.

44
00:03:14,749 --> 00:03:17,383
Even if we see each other every day,
I'll still...

45
00:03:17,383 --> 00:03:20,867
Do this.

46
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:23,175
Until you get tired of me.

47
00:03:24,326 --> 00:03:26,299
I'll never get tired of you.

48
00:03:26,299 --> 00:03:28,969
Now it's my turn to encourage you.

49
00:03:29,717 --> 00:03:31,777
Now that everything has settled down,

50
00:03:31,777 --> 00:03:34,029
we finally get to be together again.

51
00:03:34,029 --> 00:03:34,954
I'm ticklish!

52
00:03:34,954 --> 00:03:39,450
I don't want this time of happiness to end.

53
00:04:39,574 --> 00:04:40,561
Alright, everyone.

54
00:04:40,561 --> 00:04:42,936
Let's say it together.

55
00:04:42,936 --> 00:04:44,122
Eggs!

56
00:04:44,122 --> 00:04:46,229
Caterpillar!

57
00:04:46,229 --> 00:04:48,054
Pupa!

58
00:04:48,054 --> 00:04:50,555
Butterfly!

59
00:04:53,642 --> 00:04:55,455
Ready to go?

60
00:04:55,455 --> 00:04:56,984
Yeah.

61
00:05:02,882 --> 00:05:04,959
Are we missing anyone today?

62
00:05:04,959 --> 00:05:07,140
We're missing Sun.

63
00:05:10,873 --> 00:05:13,395
Why hasn't he come to school lately?

64
00:05:13,395 --> 00:05:14,806
We want to see Sun.

65
00:05:14,806 --> 00:05:16,079
Yeah, when is he coming?

66
00:05:16,079 --> 00:05:18,208
- I want to see him too.
- I miss Sun already.

67
00:05:18,208 --> 00:05:20,028
Yeah, I want to play with Sun.

68
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:21,501
Alright.

69
00:05:21,501 --> 00:05:22,880
Take it easy.

70
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:26,782
I'll tell Little Sun
that his friends miss him, okay?

71
00:05:26,782 --> 00:05:28,445
Okay!

72
00:05:28,445 --> 00:05:29,554
Yes!

73
00:05:29,554 --> 00:05:32,158
We'll finally get to see Sun!

74
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:37,600
[Sukhum Udom Rak School]

75
00:05:43,659 --> 00:05:45,471
Hey! Sun's here!

76
00:05:45,471 --> 00:05:47,833
Yay!

77
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,997
Sun, where have you been?

78
00:05:49,997 --> 00:05:51,181
Were you sick?

79
00:05:51,181 --> 00:05:52,634
No.

80
00:05:52,634 --> 00:05:55,379
Uncle Pobmek has just been
playing the guitar for me,

81
00:05:55,379 --> 00:05:57,752
so I've been lying back and relaxing at home.

82
00:05:57,752 --> 00:05:59,698
Oh, I'm so jealous!

83
00:05:59,698 --> 00:06:03,517
Teacher Pobmek,
can you play it at school again?

84
00:06:03,517 --> 00:06:06,775
If I get the chance,
I'll play it for you, okay?

85
00:06:09,335 --> 00:06:11,461
The crepe lady is here today.

86
00:06:11,461 --> 00:06:14,065
Sun, want to come get some crepes with us?

87
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:18,935
Here.

88
00:06:19,987 --> 00:06:21,490
Thank you, Uncle.

89
00:06:22,235 --> 00:06:23,258
Come on, let's go.

90
00:06:23,258 --> 00:06:25,046
Make it quick, then go to class.

91
00:06:25,046 --> 00:06:26,465
Be careful crossing the road.

92
00:06:26,465 --> 00:06:28,702
Okay.

93
00:06:30,044 --> 00:06:33,132
It's actually nice to let Sun
come to school on some days.

94
00:06:33,132 --> 00:06:34,635
Yeah.

95
00:06:34,635 --> 00:06:38,070
I guess we have to take things slow,
like we discussed.

96
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:45,346
Shit! There's a special meeting today.

97
00:06:45,346 --> 00:06:47,329
A special meeting? About what?

98
00:06:47,329 --> 00:06:49,112
The talent show!

99
00:06:49,112 --> 00:06:50,858
That's happening tomorrow.

100
00:06:50,858 --> 00:06:52,675
Is this a school or an activity center?

101
00:06:52,675 --> 00:06:54,882
There's an event here every month.

102
00:06:59,304 --> 00:07:03,154
Sun, why didn't you get crepes
with your friends?

103
00:07:03,154 --> 00:07:04,993
I changed my mind.

104
00:07:04,993 --> 00:07:07,015
I want to save money for toys instead.

105
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:12,596
I'm late!

106
00:07:12,596 --> 00:07:15,364
Make way, kids!

107
00:07:22,032 --> 00:07:24,407
We have a meeting before homeroom.

108
00:07:24,407 --> 00:07:26,887
Why aren't you there yet?

109
00:07:26,887 --> 00:07:27,972
You're right.

110
00:07:27,972 --> 00:07:29,347
Thanks for reminding us.

111
00:07:29,347 --> 00:07:30,706
I'm going.

112
00:07:32,314 --> 00:07:33,539
So?

113
00:07:33,539 --> 00:07:35,393
Well...

114
00:07:35,393 --> 00:07:37,306
You're the last one to show up.

115
00:07:37,306 --> 00:07:38,323
Hey!

116
00:07:38,323 --> 00:07:39,414
Wait for me!

117
00:07:39,414 --> 00:07:41,770
I was the one who reminded you!

118
00:07:47,636 --> 00:07:52,557
The annual talent show is tomorrow!

119
00:07:52,557 --> 00:07:57,457
We'll have a run-through this afternoon
for the kids to rehearse on stage.

120
00:07:57,457 --> 00:08:01,264
Teacher Pobmek, please run the stage
instead of Teacher Solar.

121
00:08:01,264 --> 00:08:02,151
Okay.

122
00:08:02,151 --> 00:08:05,801
And Teacher Jee,
you'll help him out like last time.

123
00:08:05,801 --> 00:08:10,932
Please keep it balanced.
No need to be too perfect.

124
00:08:10,932 --> 00:08:14,499
If I try to make things too perfect,
I'll let Teacher Pobmek deal with me.

125
00:08:14,499 --> 00:08:17,602
If Teacher Jee gets too fussy
or the OCD kicks in,

126
00:08:17,602 --> 00:08:19,840
I'll start counting for him to hear.

127
00:08:20,973 --> 00:08:22,904
What's Teacher Pobmek talking about?

128
00:08:22,904 --> 00:08:26,064
One, two, three, eight!

129
00:08:26,064 --> 00:08:27,477
Hey!

130
00:08:27,477 --> 00:08:29,754
Don't skip numbers like that!

131
00:08:30,855 --> 00:08:34,821
In sync from the start, huh?

132
00:08:35,924 --> 00:08:39,406
But do we really need two people
to run the stage?

133
00:08:39,406 --> 00:08:42,574
Right? It's just supervising the kids.

134
00:08:42,574 --> 00:08:45,079
It's not like we're performing ourselves.

135
00:08:45,946 --> 00:08:47,920
Nothing will probably happen.

136
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:50,200
[Talent Stage]

137
00:08:58,355 --> 00:09:00,253
Are your drumsticks broken?

138
00:09:01,010 --> 00:09:02,667
Can you use your hands for now?

139
00:09:04,038 --> 00:09:05,609
Line up.

140
00:09:05,609 --> 00:09:07,333
Okay.

141
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:09,253
Line up first.

142
00:09:11,142 --> 00:09:12,568
Here.

143
00:09:13,618 --> 00:09:15,473
Can you use these instead?

144
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,290
No, right?

145
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:21,262
I found the drumsticks.

146
00:09:27,534 --> 00:09:30,600
Teachers! Nobel broke my wing!

147
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,281
- I didn't.
- That's not true.

148
00:09:32,281 --> 00:09:33,387
- It's true.
- Not true!

149
00:09:33,387 --> 00:09:34,827
- It's true!
- Not true!

150
00:09:34,827 --> 00:09:37,979
- You're lying.
- Teachers, he must be punished!

151
00:09:39,971 --> 00:09:41,424
Narak.

152
00:09:42,497 --> 00:09:43,690
I got you new wings!

153
00:09:43,690 --> 00:09:45,735
No, I don't want them!

154
00:09:45,735 --> 00:09:46,821
Hey, try them on.

155
00:09:46,821 --> 00:09:47,846
You can fly with these. See?

156
00:09:47,846 --> 00:09:49,220
Narak!

157
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,381
Here you go.

158
00:09:52,381 --> 00:09:54,181
Thank you.

159
00:09:58,696 --> 00:10:00,224
Done.

160
00:10:06,020 --> 00:10:07,646
Bye-bye!

161
00:10:07,646 --> 00:10:09,659
- Bye-bye!
- Bye-bye!

162
00:10:17,267 --> 00:10:20,331
So much for "nothing will probably happen".

163
00:10:20,331 --> 00:10:22,395
That was way more than nothing.

164
00:10:22,395 --> 00:10:25,980
I forgot the kids at this school
are something else.

165
00:10:28,713 --> 00:10:30,664
Can I perform too?

166
00:10:30,664 --> 00:10:32,356
Hey, Little Sun.

167
00:10:32,356 --> 00:10:34,124
You want to be on stage too?

168
00:10:34,124 --> 00:10:36,145
What are you going to perform?

169
00:10:41,962 --> 00:10:44,284
With this little lion?

170
00:10:45,532 --> 00:10:47,966
Huh? You're performing too, Sun?

171
00:10:47,966 --> 00:10:51,273
Let's watch his rehearsal
from in front of the stage.

172
00:10:51,273 --> 00:10:53,401
- Yeah.
- Hold on.

173
00:10:53,401 --> 00:10:55,655
Sun's not performing tomorrow.

174
00:10:56,649 --> 00:10:59,807
Oh? Why not?

175
00:10:59,807 --> 00:11:04,371
I know.
It's because Sun came to school today.

176
00:11:04,371 --> 00:11:07,582
Tomorrow, Teacher Solar will come instead.

177
00:11:07,582 --> 00:11:09,576
Am I right?

178
00:11:10,546 --> 00:11:12,854
Aurora is right.

179
00:11:12,854 --> 00:11:15,761
Can I perform today, then?

180
00:11:24,647 --> 00:11:26,003
Fine.

181
00:11:26,765 --> 00:11:28,656
Go ahead.

182
00:11:28,656 --> 00:11:31,100
Yay!

183
00:11:44,151 --> 00:11:48,278
Next up is the special performance
by Grade 2 Class 1.

184
00:11:48,278 --> 00:11:52,274
Let's give it up for Little Sun!

185
00:12:12,692 --> 00:12:15,964
Why do you look so sad, Sun?

186
00:12:20,268 --> 00:12:22,475
I'm lonely, Solar.

187
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:27,852
No one's really home much.

188
00:12:27,852 --> 00:12:30,153
I don't know where everyone went.

189
00:12:30,996 --> 00:12:32,890
When no one's around,

190
00:12:35,088 --> 00:12:37,253
I'm not happy at all.

191
00:12:40,028 --> 00:12:42,624
But you have me.

192
00:12:42,624 --> 00:12:45,175
Even if it's just the two of us,

193
00:12:45,990 --> 00:12:48,466
I can take you out.

194
00:12:48,466 --> 00:12:49,774
Really?

195
00:12:50,746 --> 00:12:52,360
How are you taking me?

196
00:12:57,458 --> 00:12:59,118
Alright, everyone.

197
00:12:59,854 --> 00:13:01,671
Close your eyes.

198
00:13:11,519 --> 00:13:14,432
I'm taking you to the beach.

199
00:13:14,432 --> 00:13:16,286
Have you ever seen one?

200
00:13:20,849 --> 00:13:23,326
Imagine this.

201
00:13:23,326 --> 00:13:28,858
In front of you is the blue sea,

202
00:13:28,858 --> 00:13:31,083
a cream-colored beach,

203
00:13:32,101 --> 00:13:34,120
and white clouds.

204
00:13:36,558 --> 00:13:40,720
The waves go whoosh, whoosh.

205
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:44,681
Your feet are dipped in the water.

206
00:13:45,630 --> 00:13:48,788
How does it feel? Cold, right?

207
00:13:49,550 --> 00:13:54,480
The sea, the sand, and the clouds

208
00:13:55,738 --> 00:13:58,186
have something to tell you.

209
00:13:59,963 --> 00:14:03,581
Can we be your friends?

210
00:14:09,932 --> 00:14:11,342
Yeah.

211
00:14:12,873 --> 00:14:14,338
Of course.

212
00:14:15,369 --> 00:14:16,919
That's great.

213
00:14:17,912 --> 00:14:22,152
From now on,
you won't be lonely anymore, Sun.

214
00:14:22,152 --> 00:14:23,570
Got it?

215
00:14:24,498 --> 00:14:25,977
Got it.

216
00:14:27,087 --> 00:14:29,092
Thank you so much, Solar.

217
00:14:31,941 --> 00:14:33,745
Alright, everyone.

218
00:14:33,745 --> 00:14:35,642
Open your eyes.

219
00:14:40,390 --> 00:14:42,049
I have to go.

220
00:14:42,049 --> 00:14:46,143
Bye-bye.

221
00:15:01,964 --> 00:15:03,777
Alright.

222
00:15:03,777 --> 00:15:05,114
Thank you.

223
00:15:13,749 --> 00:15:15,600
Is something wrong?

224
00:15:21,403 --> 00:15:23,170
Yes.

225
00:15:23,170 --> 00:15:25,954
My mom called to complain
about the home renovation contractor.

226
00:15:27,004 --> 00:15:30,360
I'm so worried
she'll run into a scammer one day.

227
00:15:45,549 --> 00:15:51,574
This lunch box of Teacher Solar's is so cute.

228
00:15:52,629 --> 00:15:54,207
- What?
- So cute.

229
00:15:54,207 --> 00:15:56,007
What?

230
00:15:56,608 --> 00:16:00,097
Playing with Sun's stuff like this
could get you scolded.

231
00:16:00,097 --> 00:16:01,445
No, I won't.

232
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:04,584
Oh, I have something to show you.

233
00:16:08,898 --> 00:16:11,811
Sun came up with this himself, you know?

234
00:16:11,811 --> 00:16:13,149
Isn't that cool?

235
00:16:14,356 --> 00:16:17,770
Yeah, Sun looks happy.

236
00:16:25,643 --> 00:16:26,938
Nom.

237
00:16:34,053 --> 00:16:35,864
Where's my dessert?

238
00:16:44,605 --> 00:16:46,688
That's my dessert.

239
00:16:56,147 --> 00:17:03,244
You're late! You're late! You're late!

240
00:17:03,244 --> 00:17:05,349
How am I late every single day?

241
00:17:05,349 --> 00:17:07,300
You're not late.

242
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:09,625
I set the alarm early.

243
00:17:09,625 --> 00:17:11,690
It's show day.

244
00:17:11,690 --> 00:17:13,598
- We need to hurry up.
- Okay.

245
00:17:13,598 --> 00:17:16,373
I'll go get the car
and wait for you in front of the lobby.

246
00:17:16,373 --> 00:17:18,173
Yeah.

247
00:17:28,089 --> 00:17:29,685
What did you forget this time?

248
00:17:37,335 --> 00:17:39,008
I didn't forget.

249
00:17:40,891 --> 00:17:44,073
Go! Go now!

250
00:17:44,073 --> 00:17:45,837
Hurry!

251
00:17:45,837 --> 00:17:47,686
We don't want to be late.

252
00:18:00,753 --> 00:18:02,571
This way, please.

253
00:18:06,072 --> 00:18:08,664
The front row is almost full.

254
00:18:09,844 --> 00:18:11,751
Wow.

255
00:18:11,751 --> 00:18:13,836
They all showed up in full force.

256
00:18:13,836 --> 00:18:16,499
Teacher Pobmek, Teacher Jee, are you ready?

257
00:18:16,499 --> 00:18:18,342
I've been ready since yesterday.

258
00:18:18,342 --> 00:18:19,880
Then let's do this!

259
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:23,880
[Talent Stage]

260
00:18:24,107 --> 00:18:29,684
Welcome, all parents and lovely kids!

261
00:18:31,079 --> 00:18:35,192
Are you ready for the talent show?

262
00:18:35,192 --> 00:18:37,443
Yes!

263
00:18:37,443 --> 00:18:38,709
If you're ready,

264
00:18:38,709 --> 00:18:43,896
please enjoy the performance by
our talented kids!

265
00:19:23,028 --> 00:19:25,508
I'm so sick of homework!

266
00:19:49,542 --> 00:19:50,964
Wow.

267
00:19:50,964 --> 00:19:53,019
The reference is so clear.

268
00:19:58,918 --> 00:20:01,118
This is just like in the movie.

269
00:20:01,118 --> 00:20:04,004
Teacher Pobmek, what's going on?

270
00:20:07,373 --> 00:20:10,221
♫ Bells on bobtails ring ♫

271
00:20:10,221 --> 00:20:13,050
♫ Making spirits bright ♫

272
00:20:13,050 --> 00:20:17,762
♫ What fun it is to ride and sing
a sleighing song tonight ♫

273
00:20:17,762 --> 00:20:21,274
♫ Oh! Jingle bells, jingle bells ♫

274
00:20:21,274 --> 00:20:23,986
♫ Jingle all the way ♫

275
00:20:23,986 --> 00:20:26,496
♫ Oh, what fun it is to ride ♫

276
00:20:26,496 --> 00:20:31,392
♫ In a one-horse open sleigh ♫

277
00:20:50,454 --> 00:20:52,656
Four, King, what's wrong?

278
00:20:52,656 --> 00:20:53,925
Isn't it almost your turn?

279
00:20:53,925 --> 00:20:55,268
It's Four.

280
00:20:55,268 --> 00:20:59,067
He won't go on stage
because his dad didn't show up.

281
00:20:59,067 --> 00:21:01,991
He really promised he'd come!

282
00:21:01,991 --> 00:21:04,559
Maybe your dad had something urgent come up.

283
00:21:05,324 --> 00:21:08,805
Let's perform for your friends instead.

284
00:21:08,805 --> 00:21:10,545
Is that okay?

285
00:21:10,545 --> 00:21:14,871
Four and King from Grade 2 Class 1,
please stand by next to the stage.

286
00:21:15,972 --> 00:21:17,961
It's almost time.

287
00:21:17,961 --> 00:21:19,945
Are you really not going to perform?

288
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:21,865
Teacher Solar,

289
00:21:22,599 --> 00:21:24,715
does my dad not love me?

290
00:21:24,715 --> 00:21:26,614
Don't think like that.

291
00:21:26,614 --> 00:21:28,789
I'm sure that's not true.

292
00:21:28,789 --> 00:21:31,968
But why did he leave me like this?

293
00:21:38,529 --> 00:21:40,112
How about this?

294
00:21:40,112 --> 00:21:44,555
I'll ask Principal Sodchuen
to take a video of you for your dad.

295
00:21:44,555 --> 00:21:47,212
It'll be just like he's here
watching you in person.

296
00:21:47,212 --> 00:21:48,763
Is that okay?

297
00:21:54,166 --> 00:21:56,281
Come on, let's do it.

298
00:21:57,692 --> 00:22:00,153
Let's do it!

299
00:22:06,971 --> 00:22:08,609
What happened?

300
00:22:09,648 --> 00:22:11,637
Nothing.

301
00:22:11,637 --> 00:22:13,210
We can't miss this performance.

302
00:22:13,210 --> 00:22:14,648
Come on.

303
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:26,700
More! More!

304
00:22:39,061 --> 00:22:40,604
Great job!

305
00:22:42,525 --> 00:22:44,214
Follow me.

306
00:22:47,627 --> 00:22:48,775
Wow.

307
00:22:48,775 --> 00:22:50,371
Aren't you a Sigma boy?

308
00:22:50,371 --> 00:22:52,402
You're the kids' favorite now, aren't you?

309
00:22:52,402 --> 00:22:54,860
I don't know if I'm the kids' favorite.

310
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:58,456
But Teacher Solar's favorite...

311
00:22:59,171 --> 00:23:01,385
Uncle jokes, as always.

312
00:23:04,722 --> 00:23:09,654
Anyway, thank you for
always being by my side.

313
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:11,722
Without you,

314
00:23:11,722 --> 00:23:14,979
I don't know if the kids
would've agreed to go on stage.

315
00:23:20,309 --> 00:23:21,689
Where's my reward?

316
00:23:30,943 --> 00:23:32,225
Pobmek!

317
00:23:32,225 --> 00:23:33,751
I need your help!

318
00:23:33,751 --> 00:23:35,679
Looks like the kids forgot something again.

319
00:23:35,679 --> 00:23:37,140
What?

320
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:39,216
Is there anything they won't forget?

321
00:23:40,518 --> 00:23:42,480
Come on, I'll help you.

322
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:44,206
Hey, it's okay.

323
00:23:44,206 --> 00:23:45,991
Just go down and watch the kids' performance.

324
00:23:45,991 --> 00:23:50,213
Yeah, yeah. I was busy taking videos
that I forgot to watch the kids.

325
00:23:50,213 --> 00:23:51,772
Come with me, Solar.

326
00:23:51,772 --> 00:23:53,729
- Let's go.
- Go.

327
00:24:02,054 --> 00:24:03,666
Right here?

328
00:24:04,739 --> 00:24:05,811
Alright.

329
00:24:05,811 --> 00:24:08,747
Last but not least,

330
00:24:08,747 --> 00:24:14,264
please enjoy the special performance
by Teacher Pobmek!

331
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:38,174
I'd like to dedicate this performance
to everyone.

332
00:24:38,890 --> 00:24:43,982
Especially to the one
who's always been by my side.

333
00:25:08,752 --> 00:25:14,660
♫ Every second, I will spend on you ♫

334
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:20,508
♫ However much time passes through ♫

335
00:25:20,508 --> 00:25:26,373
♫ And when the rain falls,
know I'm here next to you ♫

336
00:25:26,373 --> 00:25:30,825
♫ We'll make it together,
and that alone will do ♫

337
00:25:30,825 --> 00:25:36,981
♫ I believe that
love is a matter of the heart ♫

338
00:25:36,981 --> 00:25:42,619
♫ There is no rule that says
that we must stay apart ♫

339
00:25:42,619 --> 00:25:49,061
♫ And though love may bring a tear or two ♫

340
00:25:49,061 --> 00:25:54,759
♫ But I'll surrender to love if it is you ♫

341
00:26:20,550 --> 00:26:23,892
♫ Let our story be written in our hearts ♫

342
00:26:23,892 --> 00:26:26,835
♫ 'Cause this love is meant just for us ♫

343
00:26:26,835 --> 00:26:32,276
♫ I will never let your hand go ♫

344
00:26:32,276 --> 00:26:35,616
♫ I will paint
and fill the storyline with you ♫

345
00:26:35,616 --> 00:26:39,142
♫ No matter if the sky turns dark and blue ♫

346
00:26:39,142 --> 00:26:46,402
♫ I will remain right here
beside you, always ♫

347
00:26:46,402 --> 00:26:47,893
Dad!

348
00:26:54,971 --> 00:26:58,849
♫ Always ♫

349
00:27:11,072 --> 00:27:12,716
Let's give another round of applause

350
00:27:12,716 --> 00:27:16,453
for Teacher Pobmek and Teacher Solar!

351
00:27:18,069 --> 00:27:19,487
Teacher Pobmek!

352
00:27:19,487 --> 00:27:20,860
Teacher Solar!

353
00:27:20,860 --> 00:27:22,152
Teacher Pobmek!

354
00:27:22,152 --> 00:27:23,469
Teacher Solar!

355
00:27:23,469 --> 00:27:24,890
Teacher Pobmek!

356
00:27:24,890 --> 00:27:26,446
Teacher Solar!

357
00:27:26,446 --> 00:27:27,950
Teacher Pobmek!

358
00:27:27,950 --> 00:27:29,176
Teacher Solar!

359
00:27:29,176 --> 00:27:30,401
Teacher Pobmek!

360
00:27:30,401 --> 00:27:31,947
Teacher Solar!

361
00:27:31,947 --> 00:27:33,300
Teacher Pobmek!

362
00:27:33,300 --> 00:27:41,543
Teacher Solar! Teacher Pobmek!

363
00:27:41,543 --> 00:27:43,270
Teacher Solar!

364
00:27:54,790 --> 00:27:56,321
Solar.

365
00:28:01,038 --> 00:28:02,518
To Ms. Pranee, please take care of him.
I can't do this anymore. - Sarun]

366
00:28:07,050 --> 00:28:08,486
Solar.

367
00:28:10,975 --> 00:28:14,469
Uncle, why am I here?

368
00:28:16,996 --> 00:28:18,394
Sun?

369
00:28:29,239 --> 00:28:31,469
Teacher Solar!

370
00:28:40,643 --> 00:28:42,030
Sun!

371
00:28:51,267 --> 00:28:55,615
Having you is the reason I lost everything!

372
00:28:55,615 --> 00:28:58,328
Teacher Solar, does my dad not love me?

373
00:28:58,328 --> 00:29:00,809
Why did he leave me like this?

374
00:29:00,809 --> 00:29:16,874
Teacher Solar! Teacher Solar!

375
00:29:16,874 --> 00:29:19,386
- Teacher Solar! Teacher Solar!
- Sun.

376
00:29:19,386 --> 00:29:25,140
Sun.

377
00:29:34,292 --> 00:29:36,162
Uncle's here.

378
00:29:37,448 --> 00:29:39,303
You don't need to be scared anymore.

379
00:29:40,248 --> 00:29:41,938
Just breathe slowly.

380
00:30:07,076 --> 00:30:08,405
Uncle,

381
00:30:10,966 --> 00:30:13,254
I don't know what's wrong with me.

382
00:30:16,547 --> 00:30:18,783
I'm so scared.

383
00:30:25,909 --> 00:30:27,531
It's okay, Sun.

384
00:30:28,439 --> 00:30:30,215
I'm right here.

385
00:30:37,745 --> 00:30:39,221
It's okay.

386
00:30:52,776 --> 00:30:56,288
That sounds like a panic attack.

387
00:30:57,623 --> 00:30:59,564
I've heard about it.

388
00:31:00,259 --> 00:31:02,959
The symptoms are just like
what you described.

389
00:31:04,052 --> 00:31:06,259
Usually,

390
00:31:06,259 --> 00:31:08,618
it's caused by built-up stress.

391
00:31:10,570 --> 00:31:13,473
Solar has probably been
trying to suppress it,

392
00:31:14,650 --> 00:31:16,394
and didn't want us to know.

393
00:31:19,049 --> 00:31:21,841
How did things go at the event?

394
00:31:21,841 --> 00:31:24,107
Forget about that.

395
00:31:25,311 --> 00:31:27,851
You don't need to worry.

396
00:31:27,851 --> 00:31:30,271
No one's blaming you at all.

397
00:31:35,547 --> 00:31:39,078
But how are you?

398
00:31:40,208 --> 00:31:41,588
Are you okay?

399
00:31:53,717 --> 00:31:55,413
I...

400
00:32:00,227 --> 00:32:02,883
I don't know what happened.

401
00:32:04,846 --> 00:32:09,165
I thought Solar was about to recover...

402
00:32:11,551 --> 00:32:14,650
because he really seemed better.

403
00:32:20,350 --> 00:32:22,280
But I don't know why...

404
00:32:25,081 --> 00:32:28,284
I don't know why
everything's gotten this much worse.

405
00:32:29,506 --> 00:32:34,530
Suddenly, Solar turned into Sun,
even though he didn't fall asleep.

406
00:32:43,249 --> 00:32:47,588
Is what I'm doing wrong?

407
00:32:54,631 --> 00:32:57,792
I don't want to say this.

408
00:33:02,861 --> 00:33:04,795
I'm so damn tired.

409
00:33:08,268 --> 00:33:11,356
I'm exhausted from taking care of Solar
the way he is now.

410
00:33:17,259 --> 00:33:19,078
Now that I've said it out loud,

411
00:33:22,545 --> 00:33:24,392
I feel even more guilty.

412
00:33:27,639 --> 00:33:30,323
I feel guilty
that I think this way about him.

413
00:33:34,665 --> 00:33:35,955
Pobmek.

414
00:33:36,998 --> 00:33:41,992
What you're feeling... isn't wrong at all.

415
00:33:43,165 --> 00:33:45,160
It's understandable.

416
00:33:48,212 --> 00:33:52,694
Taking care of someone who's unwell
is exhausting.

417
00:33:54,788 --> 00:33:57,772
But so far,

418
00:33:59,754 --> 00:34:02,497
you've done a really great job.

419
00:34:06,245 --> 00:34:08,476
If it's too much, it's too much.

420
00:34:10,041 --> 00:34:13,169
If you're tired, you're tired.

421
00:34:15,952 --> 00:34:18,768
There's nothing to feel guilty about.

422
00:34:23,053 --> 00:34:26,779
You've done really well already, Pobmek.

423
00:34:52,146 --> 00:34:53,674
It's okay.

424
00:34:57,899 --> 00:35:01,165
Why are you such a crybaby
when you're so amazing?

425
00:35:03,989 --> 00:35:05,784
Come here.

426
00:35:31,015 --> 00:35:32,371
You're up?

427
00:35:33,324 --> 00:35:34,715
How are you feeling?

428
00:35:38,608 --> 00:35:40,120
I...

429
00:35:42,720 --> 00:35:44,605
I caused trouble again, didn't I?

430
00:35:50,650 --> 00:35:51,956
I'm sorry.

431
00:35:57,563 --> 00:36:00,863
For telling you I was fine.

432
00:36:02,964 --> 00:36:05,124
I didn't tell you...

433
00:36:06,658 --> 00:36:08,381
that actually,

434
00:36:11,909 --> 00:36:13,516
I wasn't okay.

435
00:36:19,769 --> 00:36:21,569
In my mind...

436
00:36:23,935 --> 00:36:25,863
I wanted to be strong.

437
00:36:27,162 --> 00:36:29,243
I wanted to be okay.

438
00:36:32,474 --> 00:36:33,952
To be okay for you,

439
00:36:36,350 --> 00:36:38,939
so you wouldn't have to be tired
because of me anymore.

440
00:36:41,568 --> 00:36:43,037
But in the end,

441
00:36:46,965 --> 00:36:48,626
I couldn't do it.

442
00:36:54,842 --> 00:36:56,686
It's totally okay.

443
00:36:59,047 --> 00:37:01,133
It's okay if you're not strong.

444
00:37:02,684 --> 00:37:05,033
It's okay if you can't do it.

445
00:37:18,574 --> 00:37:20,568
I have something to show you.

446
00:37:37,167 --> 00:37:39,680
There's one more thing I haven't told you.

447
00:37:40,996 --> 00:37:44,483
I just found a letter your father sent me

448
00:37:44,483 --> 00:37:46,842
after he asked me to take care of you.

449
00:37:46,842 --> 00:37:51,388
It's the first and only letter he ever sent.

450
00:37:52,289 --> 00:37:53,416
Mom.

451
00:37:54,706 --> 00:37:57,160
Can you send me that letter?

452
00:37:57,160 --> 00:37:58,320
[To Ms. Pranee,
please take care of him for me.]

453
00:37:58,320 --> 00:37:59,480
[I can't do this anymore.
- Sarun]

454
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:03,069
I think...

455
00:38:03,069 --> 00:38:07,476
my father left me
because he couldn't stand seeing the face

456
00:38:07,476 --> 00:38:09,735
of the person who caused his wife's passing.

457
00:38:09,735 --> 00:38:11,535
Solar.

458
00:38:13,271 --> 00:38:15,937
Don't interpret things
in a way that hurts yourself.

459
00:38:19,184 --> 00:38:21,380
I don't want to think like that,

460
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:25,292
but what else can I think?

461
00:38:29,507 --> 00:38:31,307
Trust me.

462
00:38:32,187 --> 00:38:34,424
You shouldn't think like that.

463
00:38:41,207 --> 00:38:43,472
There were a lot of parents' cars today,

464
00:38:43,472 --> 00:38:45,795
so I parked my car across the street.

465
00:38:45,795 --> 00:38:48,043
Wait here.
I'll bring the car around and pick you up.

466
00:38:52,663 --> 00:38:53,817
Pobmek.

467
00:38:58,012 --> 00:39:00,031
I need your help with something.

468
00:39:13,112 --> 00:39:15,531
Since the accident,

469
00:39:15,531 --> 00:39:17,736
I haven't dared to cross the road again.

470
00:39:18,559 --> 00:39:21,406
It's like I've been trying to run away
from my problems all this time.

471
00:39:21,406 --> 00:39:26,231
I can feel that Little Sun feels it too.

472
00:39:26,231 --> 00:39:27,650
So...

473
00:39:28,711 --> 00:39:30,307
I...

474
00:40:25,221 --> 00:40:26,463
Pobmek.

475
00:40:29,356 --> 00:40:31,590
I'm not going to run away
from my problems anymore.

476
00:40:41,302 --> 00:40:43,003
I'm going to see my father.

477
00:40:46,624 --> 00:40:48,145
Come with me?

478
00:41:21,858 --> 00:41:23,211
Ready?

479
00:41:33,040 --> 00:41:35,029
No matter what happens,

480
00:41:35,921 --> 00:41:38,169
I'll always be by your side.

481
00:42:02,102 --> 00:42:03,402
Sun?

482
00:42:03,402 --> 00:42:06,067
He switches to Sun
without falling asleep again?

483
00:42:06,067 --> 00:42:07,262
Dad.

484
00:42:08,151 --> 00:42:09,754
- Dad!
- Hey.

485
00:42:13,714 --> 00:42:16,253
I remember everything now, Dad.

486
00:42:18,624 --> 00:42:24,066
Without you, I don't know how I'd live.

487
00:42:24,066 --> 00:42:25,700
Thank you so much.
